{{Quote
|[[Jyr Dun'Robar]] - None equals House Avithoul when it comes to the [[slave]] trade. Let your warriors gather the slaves. But you may not keep them for yourself. These slaves are given unto Lolth, not your House. [[Avithoul]] will know how to use them best.
|High Priestess Hekta Szind's missive
}}
During the [[Darkening]] in the mid-1480s DR, Dun'Robar joined an alliance with [[House Szind]], [[House Avithoul]], and several smaller houses in the [[Sschindylryn invasion of Eveningstar]], which was orchestrated by High Priestess [[Hekta Szind]] in an effort to find the [[Thread of the Weave]] on behalf of [[Lolth]]. Matron [[Jyr Dun'Robar]] devoted her house's resources to the war, sending many soldiers to assault [[Eveningstar]] and secure the surrounding [[Underdark]].

As part of the [[Cormyr]]ean counterattack, [[Wizard of War]] [[Traegar Vadamore]] sent a team of daring [[adventurer]]s into the depths of the Underdark to find and sabotage House Dun'Robar. Cloaked with powerful [[illusion]]s disgusing them as drow servants, the surfacers found Battlemaster [[Teblyn Dun'Robar]]'s personal weapon racks and contaminated them with a fast-acting [[rust monster ichor]] that destroyed the metal. They then moved to the estate's courtyard and rang a bell in challenge (potentially encountering Matron Jyr along the way), causing the Battlemaster to arrive in a furious state and attack them without his favored weapons. With Dun'Robar sabotaged and their Battlemaster defeated by a group of mysterious drow in a public manner, the house was sent into an uproar even as their reputation for martial excellence suffered. Their suspicions of outside interference caused them to draw away from their Szind and Avithoul allies, greatly weakening the drow war effort. Just as Traegar Vadamore planned, this opened up a weakness in the drow defenses that allowed a later attack upon the [[Sschindylryn Ziggurat]] and the [[Temple of Lolth (Sschindylryn)|Temple of Lolth]] atop it.
